article.headline: Central Connecticut 63, Delaware 60
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. (AP) -- Tristan Blackwood scored 19 points and Central Connecticut held off winless Delaware for a 63-60 victory Wednesday night. Central's Obie Nwadike stole a pass with the game tied at 60-60 and 45 seconds left on the clock. Dannie Powell, fouled on a drive, scored the go-ahead point for the Blue Devils (3-5) when he hit first of two shots. The Blue Devils' Javier Mojica tipped the rebound back to Powell who was fouled again. He hit both free throws this time with 2.2 seconds left for the final margin. The Blue Devils used a 17-9 run early in the second half to take a 41-40 lead at the 12:37 mark. Momentum and the lead went back-and-forth over the next eight minutes, with Delaware (0-7) twice opening up a four-point cushion. But Central rallied after consecutive 3s by Blackwood with under 3 minutes to play. Delaware (0-7) opened the first half with a full-court press that stymied Central Connecticut's offense. The Blue Devils didn't score a field goal for the first 6:57 of the game the Blue Hens had a 28-24 lead at the break. Mojica had 15 points and nine rebounds for Central, while Nwadike had 10 and 11 respectively. Brian Johnson led Delaware with 14 points.
